                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "class": "text-base md:text-xl tracking-wider font-extralight uppercase ",
                    "value": "Hidden deep within the Bavona Valley in Switzerland‚Äôs Canton of Ticino lies Sabbione, a village seemingly untouched by time"
                }
            ]
            
        },
        {
            "type": "richtext",
            "text": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": "With its rustic stone houses, breathtaking landscapes, and rich history, Sabbione offers a rare glimpse into the past. Nestled amidst towering mountains and dense forests, this remote village is not just a relic of history but a living testament to the resilience of tradition and harmony with nature."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "img",
            "title": "",
            "img": {
                "url": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/elbatista/wosdata/master/data/posts/sabbione/capa.jpeg",
                "style": {},
                "caption": "Sabbione, a hidden gem in the Bavona Valley of Ticino, Switzerland."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "richtext",
            "title": "A Step Back in Time",
            "titlelevel": 2,
            "text": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": "Sabbione‚Äôs history stretches back thousands of years, with evidence of human habitation in the Bavona Valley dating as far back as 5,000 years ago. The village itself, preserved in its "
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "class": "font-bold",
                    "value": "16th-century form"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": ", showcases remarkable "
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "class": "font-bold",
                    "value": "stone architecture"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": ". Houses built from local granite blend seamlessly into the rugged landscape, with some even constructed "
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "class": "font-bold",
                    "value": "beneath massive boulders"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": ", creating a unique and enchanting atmosphere."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "richtext",
            "text": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": "These ingenious stone structures were not only practical but also a testament to the resourcefulness of the villagers, who used the abundant local materials to build sturdy homes that could withstand the harsh alpine weather. Walking through Sabbione feels like stepping into a "
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "class": "font-bold",
                    "value": "medieval storybook"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": ", where every corner tells a tale of resilience and ingenuity."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "gallery",
            "class": "float-right w-1/2 ml-5 mt-5",
            "caption": "Stone houses in Sabbione, blending seamlessly into the natural landscape.",
            "photos": [
                {
                    "src": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/elbatista/wosdata/master/data/posts/sabbione/photo/IMG_9773.jpeg",
                    "width": 975,
