                    "url": "https://goo.gl/maps/4aHbkH4NA5b4SxiC7",
                    "target": "_blank"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": ", followed by "
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "class": "font-bold",
                    "value": "bus 333"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": " to Sabbione. Note that bus 333 operates only a few times a day, so be sure to "
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "class": "font-bold",
                    "value": "check the schedule in advance"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": ". The entire trip takes approximately 1 hour from Locarno. On weekends, buses can be crowded, and standing may be necessary. "
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "class": "font-bold",
                    "value": "Don't forget to verify the return bus schedule."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "richtext",
            "title": "By Car",
            "titlelevel": 3,
            "text": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": "You can drive directly to Sabbione, which is about a 40-minute drive from Locarno. There is a small free parking lot in front of the village ‚Äì GPS coordinates: "
                },
                {
                    "type": "link",
                    "value": "46.367288, 8.564875",
                    "url": "https://maps.app.goo.gl/nGhEnRGMkhtPf9T77",
                    "target": "_blank"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": ". The scenic drive offers breathtaking views of the Bavona Valley, making the journey as enjoyable as the destination."
                }
            ]
        },


        {
            "type": "richtext",
            "title": "Conclusion",
            "titlelevel": 2,
            "text": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "value": "Sabbione is more than just a village; it‚Äôs a journey into the heart of a bygone era. With its rich history, stunning landscapes, and timeless charm, it offers a unique experience for travelers seeking serenity and authenticity. Whether you‚Äôre drawn to its medieval architecture, its harmonious connection with nature, or simply the chance to slow down, Sabbione is a destination that lingers in the heart and mind."
                }
            ]
